org.json.write

Interface StructureWriter

  • All Superinterfaces:
    StructureIdentifier
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    NullStructureWriter, SimpleStructureWriter

    public interface StructureWriter
extends StructureIdentifier
    Strategy interface for writing a JSON structure, either a JSON Object or a JSON Array. A strategy class can implement a compact or a pretty-print output.

      • getStructureType

        char getStructureType()
        Returns the type of this structure as a char value. The values, by convention, are:
        • 'i' — the initial structure, before any JSON Object or JSON Array has been written
        • 'o' — a JSON Object
        • 'a' — a JSON Array
        Returns:
        the type of this structure, as a char value
